main event: Two bright lights were observed moving slowly across the horizon in Big Sur, California.
interesting points: The objects were described as being about the size of a softball.
The objects were moving at an estimated speed of around 60 mph.
The motion of the objects did not appear to be consistent with a small plane.
No photographs were taken of the objects.
The Air Force concluded that there was not enough data presented to indicate the objects could not have been an aircraft.
